oan request Prepares high quality, detailed credit approval documents that contain an in-depth analysis and an understanding and identification of credit issues and risks Recommends proper loan structuring that limits risk At Santander, we value and respect differences in our workforce and strive to increase the diversity of our teams. We actively encourage everyone to apply. Qualifications Bachelor's Degree (Finance, Accounting, Management, Economics or equivalent field) or equivalent work experience 3-5 years of commercial auto dealership underwriting experience Ability to work on multiple transactions simultaneously and prioritize assignments to meet deadlines and manage expectations Ability to work well on a team with different personalities, adjust quickly to various work situations, and remain composed under pressure/in stressful situations Familiarity with financial statement analysis Highly proficient with Microsoft Office, especially Excel Proven organizational skills; able to work independently and be detail oriented and thorough Strong verbal, written, interpersonal, and public presentation skills Stays current with industry and regulatory trends and emerging risk issues Has good understanding of current market and competitive landscape that the organization operates within Uses information and data effectively to support a position and present a rational case Job : Underwriting Primary Location : Texas-Dallas-1601 Elm Street - 02302 - Dallas Other Locations : Massachusetts-BOSTON-75 State Street - 06366 - State Street-Corp, New Jersey-Florham Park-200 Park Avenue - 06400 - Florham Park, New York-Melville-3 Huntington Quadrangle - 06471 - Melville, New York-New York-200 Liberty Street - 06488 - Liberty Street, Florida-Miami-1401 Brickell Avenue - 06660 - Miami Organization : CRE & MultiFamily (4701) Schedule : Full-time Job Posting : May 8, 2020, 6:35:49 PM ",
